WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:08.000
在 Apple，设计始终与伟大的想法有关
At apple, design has always been about great ideas.

2
00:00:08.100 --> 00:00:13.200
这些想法的开发过程则又充满了对细节的狂热专注
Those ideas then are developed with this obsessive dedication to detail.

3
00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:16.700
如果我们对组成产品的各种细节足够关注
If we care enough about all the details that make up a product,

4
00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:19.300
那么最后我们设计出的这种体验将使我们感觉到
then in the end we will have designed an experience

5
00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:21.900
不可能有另外的方式能够实现
that really feels like there's no other way it could be.

6
00:00:21.950 --> 00:00:25.270
最好的例子就是 macOS Big Sur
And the best example of this is MacOS Big Sur.

7
00:00:28.860 --> 00:00:32.180
我们的目标是使软件的设计更加清晰
Our goal was to bring even more clarity to the design of the software.

8
00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:36.000
同时保持 Mac 的强大功能和易用性
While retaining the Mac's, powerful capability and ease of use.

9
00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:38.500
我们从最简单的元素开始
We started with the simplest of elements,

10
00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:42.400
从圆角的半径，到按钮和控件的改良
from the shape of a corner radius to refinements in buttons and controls.

11
00:00:44.900 --> 00:00:47.500
我们把符号的统一语言引入了 Mac
And we brought our unified language of symbols to the Mac,

12
00:00:47.600 --> 00:00:51.000
使它们更统一和易于识别
making them more consistent and easier to recognize.

13
00:00:51.900 --> 00:00:54.400
使用深度、阴影和半透明
Depth, shading and translucency

14
00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.100
来创建层级
are used to create hierarchy.

15
00:00:56.100 --> 00:00:59.900
这些新材料非常丰富且充满生机
These new materials are rich and they're vibrant.

16
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.500
它们连接着明亮与黑暗
They bridge light and dark.

17
00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:07.900
我们降低了视觉复杂性，以保持对用户内容的关注
We've reduced visual complexity to keep the focus on user's content.

18
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.000
当你需要按钮和控件时，它们会出现
Buttons and controls appear when you need them,

19
00:01:10.100 --> 00:01:12.400
当你不需要时便会隐藏
and they recede when you don't.

20
00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:14.800
访问系统级控件也有着全新的方式
There's a new way to access system-level controls

21
00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:18.400
通知和小组件也有着统一的空间
and a unified space for notifications and widgets.

22
00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:20.600
我们还创建了一套新的声音。
We've also created a new suite of sounds.

23
00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:25.000
都是 Mac 上熟悉的声音，但经过重制，使其更加动听
They're familiar to the Mac, but remastered, and more refined.

24
00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:31.300
我们想让整个生态系统具有一致性
We wanted consistency throughout the ecosystem.

25
00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:34.700
这样，用户就可以在 Apple 设备之间自由切换
The users can move fluidly between the Apple devices.

26
00:01:34.800 --> 00:01:38.400
但我们也喜欢 Mac 的图标，有着深厚的历史印记
But we also love that Mac icons have a deep history

27
00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:40.500
以及独特的外观和感觉
and a distinct look and feel.

28
00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.200
所以我们保留了许多精巧的细节
So we've retained many of the highly crafted details

29
00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:48.700
以及使 Mac 图标独一无二的有趣元素
and the playful elements that make Mac icons unique.

30
00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:51.400
这个操作系统反映了重要的历史
This OS reflects an important history.

31
00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:56.300
它让人感觉熟悉，但每一个细节又是全新的
It's familiar, but it's also entirely new in every detail.

32
00:01:57.600 --> 00:01:58.500
我们喜爱 Mac
We love the Mac.

33
00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:02.600
它是我们的工具，用来创造走向世界的产品
It's the tool we use to make all the products that we put out into the world.

34
00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:05.700
macOS Big Sir 是个新的开始
And macOS Big Sir is where it starts.
